The All Progressives Congress (APC) National Campaign Council for Edo State Governorship Election has taken a swipe at Edo State Governor, Godwin Obaseki, over the endless ill treatment suffered by doctors and other health workers in the state. A statement made available to LEADERSHIP yesterday in Abuja, and signed by the spokesman for the council accused Obaseki of abdicating his basic state responsibilities, which he said has forced a three-day warning strike embarked on recently by the resident doctors in the state to the ‘’ultimate detriment’’ of Edo people who continue to bear the brunt. ‘’While it is expected of government to prioritize the health and welfare of its citizens in this pestilential time of coronavirus by committing sufficient funds to matters of health and the rebuilding of the economy imperiled by restrictions, unfortunately, in Edo State, we do not have a government truly devoted to the welfare of its people. ‘’In fact, we do not have a government, and recent events have confirmed this tragic fact. One of the most recent heart-aching development is the failure of Godwin Obaseki’s government to avert the three days strike organized by the Edo State chapter of the Association of Resident Doctors, (ARD). ‘’And thus bringing untoward hardship and suffering to patients in hospitals across the State who were already reeling from the Governor’s four years of total misrule’’, the council stated.  